1st Dia. Bad for Black
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Tahoma;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1043\f0\fs18 First you should learn why White has to play 3-3. If White just plays 1 and 3 this result is good for Black. In the normal joseki Black's stone would be at A but now Black was able to play faster.
\par That's why White has to play 3-3.\lang1042\f1
\par
\par }
